## Specialized Calculations

### Thermic Effect of Food (TEF)
```
Protein: 20-35% of calories burned in digestion
Carbs: 5-10% of calories burned in digestion  
Fat: 0-3% of calories burned in digestion

High protein diets have metabolic advantage of ~100-150 cal/day
```

### Refeed Day Calculation
```
Refeed calories = Maintenance TDEE
Refeed macros:
├── Protein: Same as diet (1g/lb)
├── Fat: Reduce to 0.3g/lb (minimum)
└── Carbs: Fill remaining calories (maximize glycogen)
```

### Reverse Diet Protocol (Post-Diet)
```
Week 1-2: Add 100 cal/day (mostly carbs)
Week 3-4: Add 100 cal/day
Continue until at maintenance TDEE
Monitor: Weight should stabilize within 2-3 lbs
```

### Body Recomposition Targets
```
For simultaneous fat loss + muscle gain:
├── Deficit: Small (10-15% below TDEE)
├── Protein: High (1.0-1.2g/lb)
├── Training: Progressive resistance required
└── Timeline: Slower than dedicated cut or bulk
```

